        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 9:27AM CST by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 927 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Richwoods, or near Arkadelphia, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arkadelphia...                    Malvern...
Gurdon...                         Rockport...
Caddo Valley...                   Poyen...
Perla...                          Whelen Springs...
Beirne...                         Gum Springs in Clark County...
Richwoods...                      Jenkins Ferry State Park...
Donaldson...                      Friendship...
Magnet Cove...                    Lono...
Curtis...                         Gifford...
Dalark...                         Midway in Hot Spring County...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
